    {
      "id": "0569cbfc54d4b00248d708af414bd29d2afd161e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 192,
        "name": "Brian Behlendorf",
        "email": "behlendorf1@llnl.gov",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-05-06 19:44:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> \"I'd think lu-object itself isn't an issue, but current approach where osd_object pins dnode?\"\n\nRight.  If the ZFS OSD were instead reworked not to keep a hold on dnodes, dbufs, or SAs from init to fini that would solve the problem.  The ARC would then be able to work as designed.  This would also be more consistent with the Posix layer where holds are only taken over the duration of a system call.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
